&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speech &amp; Language Therapy Service Manager - (Adults and Acute Paediatrics)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rare opportunity to lead and manage a group of 25 dedicated and passionate therapists who provide an integrated speech and language therapy service to adults with acquired communication and swallowing disorders in Buckinghamshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder wil be responsible for leading and delivering the speech &amp; language therapy services offered within appropriate hospital or community settings in Buckinghamshire. The role also covers management of the acute paediatric speech and language therapy service at Stoke Mandeville Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must be a qualified Speech &amp; Language Therapist and be registered with the HCPC. They will be expected to be aware of the full scope of clinical practice, to support and ensure the supervision of all speech &amp; language therapy staff and to ensure the delivery of a high quality services to patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide professional leadership and be responsible for the speech &amp; language therapy service development, strategic planning and clinical governance of the service. The service provision extends to working with stakeholders within a multi-agency framework.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will have experience of leadership of teams and an understanding of acute and community services. The role involves some clinical work in order to support the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Angela Brooke, AHP Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : angelabrooke@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number : 07771 335372&lt;/p&gt;
